[[Image:Golden Film Liever verliefd 2.jpg|thumb|250px|The Golden Film trophy for ''[[Love to Love (film)|Love to Love]]'' (2003)]]

The '''Golden Film''' ({{lang-nl|'''Gouden Film'''}}) is a [[film]] [[award]] recognising domestic [[box office]] achievements in the [[Netherlands]]. The Golden Film is awarded to films from the Netherlands once they have sold {{nowrap|100,000 tickets}}. The award is an initiative by the [[Netherlands Film Festival]] and the [[Netherlands Film Fund]] to increase media attention for [[Netherlands|Dutch]] films. Since its introduction in [[2001]], the public's interest in Dutch films in the Netherlands has increased. The Golden Film has been awarded to [[List of films that received the Golden Film|{{:List of films that received the Golden Film}}&nbsp;films]].

Dutch newspapers report about films receiving the Golden Film. Recipients consider the Golden Film to be an award for success. Critics have said that films cannot be considered successful if they have sold only the number of tickets needed to receive the award.

==Award==
A Golden Film is [[award]]ed to a [[film]] from the [[Netherlands]] once it has sold {{nowrap|100,000 [[Movie theater|cinema]]}} tickets in the Netherlands during the original cinema circulation.<ref name="film-fund-press-release">{{cite press release
  | title = Nieuwe voorwaarden Gouden en Platina Film
  | publisher = [[Netherlands Film Fund]]
  | date = [[2003-03-11]]
  | url = http://www.filmfund.nl/nieuws/046.htm
  | accessdate = 2005-12-25 }} {{nl icon}}</ref> The number of tickets sold is based on [[box office]] information provided by the film's [[film distributor|distributor]] and the [[Netherlands Association of Film Distributors]].<ref>{{cite web
  | title = De Kristallen Film, Gouden Film en Platina Film
  | work = [http://www.goudenfilm.nl www.goudenfilm.nl]
  | url = http://www.goudenfilm.nl/content/watis.html
  | accessdate = 2006-12-25 }} {{nl icon}}</ref> After a film is awarded the Golden Film, it can receive a [[Platinum Film]] for {{nowrap|400,000 tickets sold}} and a [[Diamond Film]] for {{nowrap|1,000,000 tickets sold}}. In addition to these awards, there is the [[Crystal Film]], which is awarded to [[documentary film]]s that sell more than {{nowrap|10,000 tickets}} 

The Golden Film is an initiative by the [[Netherlands Film Festival]] and the government-subsidized [[Netherlands Film Fund]], with the support of [[Film Investors Netherlands]], to increase the public's awareness of [[Netherlands|Dutch]] films in the Netherlands. The Golden Film recognises box office achievements to encourage positive publicity for a film after the initial media attention surrounding its release has begun to wane. The award is similar to the Dutch music industry's Golden Record, that is awarded after selling 40,000&nbsp;singles, 35,000&nbsp;popular music albums, or 15,000&nbsp;classical music albums.<ref name="feest">{{cite web
  | last = Ockhuysen
  | first = Ronald 
  | title = Nederlandse film viert feest
  | work = [http://www.cinema.nl/ Cinema.nl]
  | date = [[2002-10-24]]
  | url = http://www.cinema.nl/cinema/magazines/news/index.jsp?portals=3142294&magazines=5268514&news=9003314
  | accessdate = 2007-01-12 }} {{nl icon}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
  | title = Goud/Platina reglement
  | work = [http://www.nvpi.nl/ www.nvpi.nl]
  | publisher = Nederlandse Vereniging van producenten en Importeurs van beeld- en geluidsdragers
  | url = http://www.nvpi.nl/nvpi/pagina.asp?pagkey=62772&
  | accessdate = 2007-11-04 }} {{nl icon}}</ref>

The Golden Film awards are presented during small press ceremonies throughout the year and shortly after a film has reached the audience criterion. The [[trophy|trophies]] are presented by the director of the Netherlands Film Festival or sometimes by a member of the crew or cast of the film itself.<ref>{{cite web
  | title = Uitreiking Gouden Film Zwartboek
  | work = [http://www.fuworks.nl/ www.fuworks.nl]
  | publisher = [[Fu Works]]
  | date = [[2006-09-18]]
  | url = http://www.fuworks.nl/news.php?id=63
  | accessdate = 2007-08-17 }} {{nl icon}}</ref><ref>{{cite web
  | last = Zanten
  | first = Claudia van
  | title = Kruistocht in Spijkerbroek krijgt Gouden Film
  | work = [http://www.elsevier.nl/ www.elsevier.nl]
  | publisher = [[Elsevier (magazine)|Elsevier]] 
  | date = [[2006-11-27]]
  | url = http://www.elsevier.nl/nieuws/cultuur_en_televisie/artikel/asp/artnr/127954/index.html
  | accessdate = 2007-08-17 }} {{nl icon}}</ref><ref name="verliefd">{{cite news 
  | title = Gouden Film voor N Beetje Verliefd
  | work = [http://www.telegraaf.nl/ www.telegraaf.nl]
  | publisher = [[De Telegraaf]]
  | date = [[2007-01-15]]
  | url = http://www.telegraaf.nl/prive/article56869921.ece
  | accessdate = 2007-08-27 }} {{nl icon}}</ref> Two trophies are presented for each film: one to the [[film producer|producer]] and the [[Film director|director]], representing the [[film crew]], and the other to the lead [[actor]]s, representing the [[cast member|cast of the film]].<ref name="film-fund-press-release"/>

The trophy is a thick square frame, that contains a small square [[Film still|still]] from the receiving film.<ref name="crystal">{{cite web
  | title = Nieuwe prijs voor Nederlandse documentaires
  | work = [http://www.cinema.nl Cinema.nl]
  | date = [[2005-04-28]]
  | url = http://www.cinema.nl/cinema/magazines/news/index.jsp?portals=3142294&magazines=5268514&news=22154151
  | accessdate = 2007-01-11 }} {{nl icon}}</ref> The frame is made from [[Milling machine|milled]] [[wood]], which has a plate attached to it, on the first line enscribed with the text "Gouden Film", three squares, and the year, and on the second line with the film title.<ref>{{cite web
  | title = Cnc freeswerk
  | work = [http://www.speravi.nl Speravi]
  | url = http://www.speravi.nl/CNC%20freeswerk.html
  | accessdate = 2007-01-13 }} {{nl icon}}</ref>

